{{No footnotes|date=2015th year 8月}}
'''Shōshichii''' (正七位) is one of the {{ill|Court Ranks of Japan|ja|位階|12=draft|12=draft}}. It is positioned below {{ill|Junior Sixth Rank|ja|従六位|1=Junior Sixth Rank|12=draft|12=draft}} and above {{ill|Junior Seventh Rank|ja|従七位|1=Junior Seventh Rank|12=draft|12=draft}}.<ref>https://www.wakapoetry.net/background/society/court-offices-titles-and-Ranks/court-Ranks/</ref>
== Overview == Shōshichii was first established in {{ill|Taihō|ja|大宝|12=draft|12=draft}}元年 (701) as part of the {{ill|Taihō Code|ja|大宝律令|12=draft|12=draft}}, along with other Ranks. Under the {{ill|Ritsuryō system|ja|律令制|12=draft|12=draft}}, Shōshichii was further divided into two subRanks: Upper Shōshichii (正七位上) and Lower Shōshichii (正七位下). During the early {{ill|Meiji period|ja|明治時代|12=draft|12=draft}}, the {{ill|Daijōkan system (Meiji period)|ja|太政官制|12=draft|12=draft}} abolished these subRanks, and Shōshichii was equivalent to positions such as Assistant Grand Recorder (権大史) in the {{ill|Jingikan|ja|神祇官|1=Department of Divinities|blank= (明治時代)|12=draft|12=draft}} and Assistant Junior Recorder (権少史) in the {{ill|Daijōkan|ja|太政官 (明治時代)|12=draft|12=draft}}.
Until the suspension of conferring Ranks to living persons in 1946 (Shōwa 21), Shōshichii was the initial Rank for {{ill|Civil officials|ja|文官|12=draft|12=draft}} at the {{ill|Kōtōkan|ja|高等官|12=draft|12=draft}} 6th grade (e.g., police inspectors) and {{ill|Military officers|ja|武官|12=draft|12=draft}} at the Rank of captain (e.g., company commanders). After the suspension, Shōshichii was awarded posthumously, typically to local branch directors of government ministries, police officers at the inspector Rank, and similar positions.
Notable recipients of Shōshichii include {{ill|Wainai Sadayuki|ja|和井内貞行|12=draft|12=draft}}, who contributed to the development of {{ill|Lake Towada|ja|十和田湖|12=draft|12=draft}}, and {{ill|Kunihiko Miyamoto|ja|宮本邦彦 (警察官)|12=draft|12=draft}}, a Tokyo Metropolitan Police Department inspector who died in the line of duty at {{ill|Tokiwadai Station (Tokyo)|ja|ときわ台駅 (東京都)|12=draft|12=draft}} on the Tōbu Tōjō Line.
