or Seventh Rank|ja|正七位|1=Senior Seventh Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Seventh Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Seventh Rank|qq=}} {{ill|Junior Seventh Rank|ja|従七位|1=Junior Seventh Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Seventh Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Seventh Rank|qq=}} {{ill|Senior Eighth Rank|ja|正八位|1=Senior Eighth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Eighth Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Eighth Rank|qq=}} {{ill|Junior Eighth Rank|ja|従八位|1=Junior Eighth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Eighth Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Eighth Rank|qq=}} {{ill|Senior Ninth Rank|ja|正九位|1=Senior Ninth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Ninth Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Ninth Rank|qq=}} {{ill|Junior Ninth Rank|ja|従九位|1=Junior Ninth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Ninth Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Ninth Rank|qq=}} {{ill|Greater Initial Rank|ja|大初位|1=Greater Initial Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Greater Initial Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Greater Initial Rank|qq=}} {{ill|Lesser Initial Rank|ja|少初位|1=Lesser Initial Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Lesser Initial Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Lesser Initial Rank|qq=}} endRanklist--><!--Senior Seventh Rank-->

{{No footnotes|date=2015th year 8月}}

'''Shōshichii''' (正七位) is one of the {{ill|Court Ranks of Japan|ja|位階|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Court Ranks of Japan|qq=}}. It is positioned below {{ill|Junior Sixth Rank|ja|従六位|1=Junior Sixth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Sixth Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Sixth Rank|qq=}} and above {{ill|Junior Seventh Rank|ja|従七位|1=Junior Seventh Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Seventh Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Seventh Rank|qq=}}.<ref>https://www.wakapoetry.net/background/society/court-offices-titles-and-Ranks/court-Ranks/</ref>

== Overview ==
Shōshichii was first established in {{ill|Taihō|ja|大宝|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taihō|qq=}}元年 (701) as part of the {{ill|Taihō Code|ja|大宝律令|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taihō Code|qq=}}, along with other Ranks. Under the {{ill|Ritsuryō system|ja|律令制|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ritsuryō system|qq=}}, Shōshichii was further divided into two subRanks: Upper Shōshichii (正七位上) and Lower Shōshichii (正七位下). During the early {{ill|Meiji period|ja|明治|lt=Meiji period|1=Meiji era|2=ja|3=明治|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji period|qq=}}, the {{ill|Daijōkan system (Meiji period)|ja|太政官制|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Daijōkan system (Meiji period)|qq=}} abolished these subRanks, and Shōshichii was equivalent to positions such as Assistant Grand Recorder (権大史) in the {{ill|Jingikan|ja|神祇官|1=Department of Divinities|blank= (明治時代)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jingikan|13=User:Immanuelle/Department of Divinities|qq=}} and Assistant Junior Recorder (権少史) in the {{ill|Daijōkan|ja|太政官 (明治時代)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Daijōkan|qq=}}.

Until the suspension of conferring Ranks to living persons in 1946 (Shōwa 21), Shōshichii was the initial Rank for {{ill|Civil officials|ja|文官|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Civil officials|qq=}} at the {{ill|Kōtōkan|ja|高等官|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōtōkan|qq=}} 6th grade (e.g., police inspectors) and {{ill|Military officers|ja|武官|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Military officers|qq=}} at the Rank of captain (e.g., company commanders). After the suspension, Shōshichii was awarded posthumously, typically to local branch directors of government ministries, police officers at the inspector Rank, and similar positions.

Notable recipients of Shōshichii include {{ill|Wainai Sadayuki|ja|和井内貞行|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wainai Sadayuki|qq=}}, who contributed to the development of {{ill|Lake Towada|ja|十和田湖|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Lake Towada|qq=}}, and {{ill|Kunihiko Miyamoto|ja|宮本邦彦 (警察官)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kunihiko Miyamoto|qq=}}, a Tokyo Metropolitan Police Department inspector who died in the line of duty at {{ill|Tokiwadai Station (Tokyo)|ja|ときわ台駅 (東京都)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tokiwadai Station (Tokyo)|qq=}} on the Tōbu Tōjō Line.

